         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/2/86. ¶  ¶ As I have written dear Sir Joseph, while congratulating Mr Dyer, ¶  also concerning your excellent son, I shall only offer a short letter this time, expressing my particular hope, that t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.02.17a </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-1890, f. 166.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17/2/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I have written dear Sir Joseph, while congratulating Mr Dyer,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 17 February 1886.</p>
               </note> also concerning your excellent son, I shall only offer a short letter this time, expressing my particular hope, that the evening of your life will be a long and serene one, and that you will attain at last your father’s and Mr Bentham’s age, thus living into the next century!<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker retired from the directorship of Kew at the end of November 1885 and was succeeded by Thiselton-Dyer.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will do grand work now for special phytography. The new genus of <name key="Laurinae">Laurinae</name> with one celled anthers must be very interesting.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Probably <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Syndiclis, </seg>erected (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. paradoxa</seg>) by Hooker in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Hooker’s icones plantarum</seg>, vol. 16, 1886, plate 1515. However, it was described as having a one-celled ovary, not anther.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Expedition of Capt. Everill<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bonito</seg> expedition to the Fly River estuary, Papua, 1885.</p>
               </note> has <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> yielded much novelty among plants. As it was mainly a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">geographic</hi>
               </seg> expedition, and no high Mountains presented themselves at the Fly River System, mostly ordinary Malaian<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Malayan?</p>
               </note> forms, well known, were got, d’Albertis<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Luigi Maria d'Albertis.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> having also to some extent been over the ground before.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Forbes treats the Austral. geogr. Soc., after its generosity to him <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unfairly</hi>
               </seg>, unless he mends. So also the hope, so long cherished by me, to render known the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">highland</hi>
               </seg>-flora of New Guinea may become <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">blighted</hi>
               </seg>, after <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my</hi>
               </seg> writings drew mainly attention to it.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to E. Strickland, 10 October 1885; M to W. Carruthers, 21 October 1885 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>85-10-21a); and W. Carruthers to M, 1 March 1886.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I hope my geographic adress will please you; it evolves some <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ideas</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B85.13.25.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Laurinae">Laurinae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
